-- Russia Equity Movers: Polymetal, Raspadskaya, VTB Group Shares
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-07-11T15:46:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/russia-equity-movers-polymetal-raspadskaya-vtb-group-shares.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  lost 1.2
percent to 1,405.15 by the close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,355.86.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Polymetal International Plc (POLY)   tumbled 4.9 percent
to 834 pence in  London , the most since May 23. The stock fell as
a court ruled the Russian gold and silver miner will pay about
$27 million in additional taxes and fines.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX) lost 0.7 percent to 85.47 rubles,
the first decline in three days. The coal producer fell as coal
output dropped 1 percent to 3.4 million tons in the first half
of the year.  VTB Group (VTBR RX) declined 3 percent to 5.54 kopeks, the
lowest level since June 28. UBS AG added Russia’s second-largest
lender to its list of least-preferred stocks, citing the bank’s
reliance on income from trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
